<plot>Every year millions of girls the world over have their genital organs totally or partially removed. Over 140 million women are believed to have suffered this fate as part of a tradition based on beliefs and myths passed down from generation to generation, particularly on the African continent. But in countries like Ethiopia, an association fights to eradicate this practice by raising awareness on the subject.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?186947</url></doc>
